did, was ice and bake cupcakes,

00:08:54.350 --> 00:08:55.980
and I couldn't
have been happier.

00:08:55.980 --> 00:09:01.170
But we grew the business,
so now I do a lot of things.

00:09:01.170 --> 00:09:05.250
So in October, I came out
with a book that I wrote.

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:09.060
It's called "Cakes by
Melissa," and the reason

00:09:09.060 --> 00:09:10.890
that I felt like I
needed to write a book

00:09:10.890 --> 00:09:13.290
was because I had all of
these recipes in my head

00:09:13.290 --> 00:09:15.640
that I'd been using for Baked
by Melissa all the time.

00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:19.530
And even though you can't
make bite-sized cupcakes,

00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:23.820
I really wanted the
reader to be able to think

00:09:23.820 --> 00:09:27.640
the way I think and get
creative the way I create.

00:09:27.640 --> 00:09:31.420
So I think it achieved that.

00:09:31.420 --> 00:09:33.780
And it takes you through
my creative process

00:09:33.780 --> 00:09:38.700
of coming up with these
random flavor profiles,

00:09:38.700 --> 00:09:41.280
starting with a very base--

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:44.170
like vanilla cake,
as an example--

00:09:44.170 --> 00:09:45.840
and then adding one
or two ingredients.

00:09:45.840 --> 00:09:48.330
And you can make anything.

00:09:48.330 --> 00:09:51.330
If you take your
vanilla cake base

00:09:51.330 --> 00:09:54.450
and replace the liquid,
which is whole milk,

00:09:54.450 --> 00:09:57.667
with strawberry puree, you
get this bomb strawberry cake.

00:09:57.667 --> 00:09:59.250
And it's crazy, and
it's super simple.

00:09:59.250 --> 00:10:00.720
And people always
think that baking

00:10:00.720 --> 00:10:06.120
is crazy and really complicated,
but I don't think it is.

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:12.540
So the cake that I'm going
to make for you guys today

00:10:12.540 --> 00:10:16.230
is the tie-dye cake, because
that's why we're here.

00:10:16.230 --> 00:10:18.360
But we don't have a
ton of time together,

00:10:18.360 --> 00:10:23.450
so the cake is already made,
and my husband made it.

00:10:23.450 --> 00:10:25.280
He sent it to us.

00:10:25.280 --> 00:10:30.510
So it's big, so it's on one of
our sheet pans from the bakery.

00:10:30.510 --> 00:10:33.570
And I like to make my
layer cakes this way,

00:10:33.570 --> 00:10:38.090
because I don't like the crust.

00:10:38.090 --> 00:10:41.640
And obviously, in
the book, the recipe

00:10:41.640 --> 00:10:48.900
is for a quarter-sheet
pan, because that's normal.

00:10:48.900 --> 00:10:52.500
But you know, we got this one.

00:10:52.500 --> 00:10:56.800
So you wouldn't have as much
scrap as I'm going to have,

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:57.910
so don't judge.

00:10:57.910 --> 00:11:00.330
And I use the scrap to
decorate the cake too.

00:11:00.330 --> 00:11:04.500
But you take six-inch or however
big you want your cake to be--

00:11:04.500 --> 00:11:05.670
Amazon is amazing.

00:11:05.670 --> 00:11:07.830
You can get anything
you need on Amazon,

00:11:07.830 --> 00:11:09.600
and you don't have
to be a baker.

00:11:09.600 --> 00:11:10.800
You can Google recipes.

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:17.430
You could get "Cakes by Melissa"
and use those recipes and order

00:11:17.430 --> 00:11:20.020
everything you need, and
then just have a lot of fun.

00:11:20.020 --> 00:11:22.680
So I actually didn't know
that these things existed

00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:24.870
until I searched on
Amazon, because I wanted

00:11:24.870 --> 00:11:27.480
to be able to make
cakes of all sizes

00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:30.000
when I was recipe-testing.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:32.580
So I like to punch
out my layers,

00:11:32.580 --> 00:11:36.270
because then it's like the
whole cake is delicious.

00:11:36.270 --> 00:11:39.040
You know?

00:11:39.040 --> 00:11:40.190
Layer one.

00:11:40.190 --> 00:11:42.120
Got my vanilla icing.

00:11:42.120 --> 00:11:46.410
Does anyone know the three
ingredients in vanilla icing?

00:11:46.410 --> 00:11:47.609
AUDIENCE: Sugar.

00:11:47.609 --> 00:11:48.650
MELISSA BEN-ISHAY: Sugar.

00:11:48.650 --> 00:11:50.119
AUDIENCE: Butter,
sugar, vanilla.

00:11:50.119 --> 00:11:51.160
MELISSA BEN-ISHAY: Great.

00:11:51.160 --> 00:11:53.930
Butter, sugar, vanilla extract.

00:11:53.930 --> 00:11:55.530
It's so easy.

00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:58.050
I actually added a
little bit of whole milk

00:11:58.050 --> 00:12:01.639
to this, because when
I'm spreading on cake--

00:12:01.639 --> 00:12:03.180
you know how it can
get really messy?

00:12:03.180 --> 00:12:10.760
This just makes it a much
smoother consistency,

00:12:10.760 --> 00:12:11.690
and it's much--

00:12:11.690 --> 00:12:12.190
see?

00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:14.795
It's so easy.

00:12:14.795 --> 00:12:17.170
So a little icing
between each layer.

00:12:21.160 --> 00:12:23.990
So before, again, I
wanted to write a book,

00:12:23.990 --> 00:12:28.260
but I wasn't sure how I would
get the bit-sized cupcakes

00:12:28.260 --> 00:12:32.560
through in this book that I
knew I couldn't give you recipes

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:35.350
for, because it's
impossible to bake them.

